article.headline: Wagner 71, Yale 68
article.story: NEW HAVEN, Conn. (AP) -- Durell Vinson had 16 points and eight rebounds and James Ulrich added 15 points and nine boards to lead Wagner to a 71-68 win over Yale on Saturday. Jamal Smith hit a jumper while being fouled with 1:14 left to give Wagner (5-2)a 69-68 lead. He missed the free throw, but Yale could not capitalize. Matt Kyle missed an 8-foot hook shot from the baseline with 42 seconds left for Yale (1-5). The Bulldogs got the ball back with 11 seconds left, but Mark Porter stole the ball from Eric Flato about 25 feet from the Yale basket and drove in for a layup. Porter hit three 3-pointers and finished with 15 points. Travis Pinick missed a half-court attempt at the buzzer. The Bulldogs were led by Ross Morin, who had 14 points and six rebounds. Caleb Holmes added 11.
